{"id": "EUVD-2022-55570", "enisaUuid": "2c4d55a4-773d-354c-af97-7ca3f949888c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmm,hugetlb: take hugetlb_lock before decrementing h->resv_huge_pages\n\nThe h->*_huge_pages counters are protected by the hugetlb_lock, but\nalloc_huge_page has a corner case where it can decrement the counter\noutside of the lock.\n\nThis could lead to a corrupted value of h->resv_huge_pages, which we have\nobserved on our systems.\n\nTake the hugetlb_lock before decrementing h->resv_huge_pages to avoid a\npotential race.", "datePublished": "2025-09-15T15:31:25", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-04T21:31:01", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3e50a07b6a5fcd39df1534d3fdaca4292a65efe6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/629c986e19fe9481227c7cdfd9a105bbc104d245", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2b35432d324898ec41beb27031d2a1a864a4d40e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/11993652d0b49e27272db0a37aa828d8a3a4b92b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/568e3812b1778b4c0c229649b59977d88f400ece", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/112a005d1ded04a4b41b6d01833cc0bda90625cc", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c828fab903725279aa9dc6ae3d44bb7e4778f92c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/12df140f0bdfae5dcfc81800970dd7f6f632e00c", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50285"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50285"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "020f6056-cde7-325f-be75-393ec5081f1f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.9.332"}, {"id": "0bfa7652-ea84-34ba-9731-61477a96bc55", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "a88c769548047b21f76fd71e04b6a3300ff17160 <3e50a07b6a5fcd39df1534d3fdaca4292a65efe6"}, {"id": "0c0a93c3-7908-3153-a791-47c5c7a7422e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1"}, {"id": "35d11599-4796-342a-91c5-a729dc41ff0c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "412b6508-12c4-36b7-96cc